EU Summit Argues Over Refugee Policy, EU Official: Bottlenecks at Every Step of the Reception Process - China News Network
EU Summit endlessly argues over refugee policy, EU official: there are bottlenecks at every step of the reception process
[Global Times special correspondent in Belgium, Niu Ruifei] According to a report by Agence France-Presse on February 10, at the latest EU summit that day, the President of the European Commission, Ursula von der Leyen, stated that EU leaders agreed to implement stricter policies on illegal immigration, making it easier to deport illegal immigrants.
The report said that this move by the EU is a response to the growing concern about the problem of illegal immigration in Europe. Now, the core issue for the EU is that very few illegal immigrants can ultimately be deported.
